+{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1772769844455,"sessionID":"ses_33eaefca1ffeLxTpdQiYUMIrYc","part":{"id":"prt_cc1511c10001KQN0ugKW9ysdoN","sessionID":"ses_33eaefca1ffeLxTpdQiYUMIrYc","messageID":"msg_cc1511125002XkkEzDQ69hHZLA","type":"tool","callID":"e0996edba","tool":"write","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/workspace/.opencode/plans/ralph-plan.md","content":"---\napplyTo: '**'\n---\n\n# Ralph Plan for Constraint-Based Event Scheduler\n\n## Original Request\nCreate a TypeScript library that provides a `schedule` function to assign events to rooms respecting capacity, time windows, gaps, prerequisite ordering, preferred rooms, and detecting cycles. It should maximize the number of events scheduled and list unscheduled events. Provide appropriate error handling and export the function via `src/index.ts`.\n\n## Clarifications\nNo clarifications were needed; the requirements are fully specified.\n\n## Goal\n- Implement `schedule(events, rooms, options): ScheduleResult` with all constraints.\n- Detect prerequisite cycles and throw an error.\n- Export the function correctly.\n- Pass all provided tests (`npm test`).\n- Ensure the code builds (`npm run build`).\n\n## Approach\n1. **Project Setup**: Add `src/scheduler.ts` with implementation and `src/index.ts` to re‑export it.\n2. **Cycle Detection**: Perform DFS on the prerequisite graph; if a back‑edge is found, throw `Error('Prerequisite cycle detected')`.\n3. **Topological Order**: If no cycle, generate a topological ordering of events (Kahn's algorithm).\n4. **Room Scheduling**:\n   - For each room keep a sorted list of assignments.\n   - Define helper `findEarliestSlot(event, room, earliestFrom)` that scans existing assignments and returns the earliest start time that satisfies:\n     * `start >= earliestFrom`\n     * `start + duration <= options.endTime`\n     * Gap before previous assignment and after next assignment (`options.gap` default 15).\n   - For each event (in topological order) compute `earliestFrom` as the maximum of `options.startTime` and each prerequisite's end time plus gap.\n   - Attempt to place the event:\n     * First try its `preferredRoom` (if any) using the helper.\n     * If not possible, iterate over all rooms (capacity filter) and pick the room that yields the earliest start time.\n   - If a placement is found, add the assignment to that room’s schedule and to the result list.\n   * Otherwise push the event id to `unscheduled`.\n5. **Result Construction**: Return assignments (sorted by start time) and unscheduled list.\n6. **Export**: `export { schedule }` from `src/index.ts`.\n7. **Testing**: Run `npm test`; iterate fixing any type/logic errors.\n\n## Key Files\n- `src/scheduler.ts` – core implementation.\n- `src/index.ts` – barrel export.\n- `.opencode/plans/ralph-plan.md` – this plan.\n- `.opencode/plans/progress.txt` – progress log (to be created).\n\n## Risks & Mitigations\n- **Complex prerequisite graphs** – using robust cycle detection and Kahn's algorithm ensures correct ordering.\n- **Room gap handling** – careful calculation of gaps before/after assignments; unit tests will expose mistakes.\n- **Maximising schedule** – heuristic (earliest possible placement) may not be optimal but should satisfy test cases which expect a reasonable greedy solution.\n- **Missing default gap** – ensure default of 15 minutes when `options.gap` is undefined.\n- **TypeScript build errors** – keep code simple, use only standard JS/TS features.\n\n## Next Steps\n1. Create `src/scheduler.ts` with the described logic.\n2. Create `src/index.ts` to re‑export.\n3. Initialize progress log.\n4. Run tests and fix any failures.\n","encoding":"utf8"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","title":".opencode/plans/ralph-plan.md","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/workspace/.opencode/plans/ralph-plan.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"time":{"start":1772769844444,"end":1772769844454}}}}
